You are working on ProcureAI, an AI-powered procurement platform for small businesses.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.12+), async-first
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL) with pgvector
- AI: Anthropic Claude API, LangGraph for orchestration
- Frontend: Next.js 15, React 19, Tailwind CSS
- Email: Resend
- Scraping: Firecrawl

## Coding Standards
- Use Pydantic v2 for ALL schemas and data validation
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 async ORM for database models
- All FastAPI endpoints must be async
- Type hints everywhere — no `Any` without justification
- Agent prompts stored as Markdown files in `app/agents/prompts/`
- Agent outputs must be Pydantic models (typed, validated)
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` for all HTTP calls (never `requests`)

## Architecture
- LangGraph orchestrator in `app/agents/orchestrator.py`
- Each agent is a separate module in `app/agents/`
- Agent tools in `app/agents/tools/`
- State flows through `GraphState` TypedDict between agents
- In-memory project store for MVP (migrate to Supabase later)

## Patterns
- Structured JSON output from LLMs — always validate with Pydantic
- Parallel fan-out for multi-source searches
- Error boundaries per agent — never let one agent crash the pipeline
- Human-in-the-loop checkpoints before outreach and final recommendations
